## 5. CODING RULES

### General
- TypeScript strict mode — `no any`, explicit return types on all functions
- No default exports from component files — named exports only (except page.tsx)
- Every component receives props via a typed interface: `interface ComponentNameProps {}`
- Max file length: 200 lines — split into sub-components if exceeded
- Every async server function must have try/catch with typed error handling

### Components
```tsx
// CORRECT — named export, typed props, mobile-first
interface ScoreChipProps {
  value: number
  date: string
  isActive?: boolean
  isEmpty?: boolean
  isOldest?: boolean
  onEdit?: () => void
  onDelete?: () => void
}

export function ScoreChip({
  value,
  date,
  isActive = false,
  isEmpty = false,
  isOldest = false,
  onEdit,
  onDelete,
}: ScoreChipProps) {
  // implementation
}
```

### Styling Rules
- Tailwind utility classes first
- Custom CSS only in `globals.css` via CSS variables
- Never hardcode brand hex values in component files — always use Tailwind color tokens
- Mobile-first: base styles = mobile, `md:` and `lg:` for larger screens
- All interactive elements minimum 44px touch target on mobile

### Server vs Client
```
'use server'  → all data fetching, mutations, Supabase server calls
'use client'  → Framer Motion, useState, useEffect, Zustand, form interactions
```

### Supabase Pattern
```ts
// Always use server client for mutations
import { createServerClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'

// Always handle RLS errors explicitly
const { data, error } = await supabase.from('scores').select('*')
if (error) throw new Error(`Score fetch failed: ${error.message}`)
```

