## 6. DATABASE RULES

### Schema Reference
```sql
-- Core tables (always reference these exact names)
profiles          -- extends auth.users
scores            -- rolling 5 per user, unique date per user
charities         -- charity directory
draws             -- monthly draws
draw_entries      -- snapshot of user scores at draw time
winners           -- verified winners
subscription_events -- Stripe webhook audit log
```

### Score Rolling Logic (critical — enforce always)
```ts
// Before inserting a new score:
// 1. Count existing scores for user
// 2. If count >= 5, delete the oldest (by score_date ASC)
// 3. Check for duplicate date — reject with error if exists
// 4. Insert new score
// This logic lives in: /lib/draw-engine/matcher.ts
```

### RLS Policy Rules
- Users can only read/write their own rows — enforce via `auth.uid() = user_id`
- Admin operations use service role key — server-side only, never expose to client
- Subscription status check on every authenticated request via middleware

