## 7. STRIPE RULES

### Webhook Handler (critical path)
```ts
// /app/api/webhooks/stripe/route.ts
// Must handle ALL of these events:
// - invoice.paid               → activate subscription
// - customer.subscription.updated → update plan
// - customer.subscription.deleted → mark as cancelled
// - invoice.payment_failed     → mark as lapsed
// Always verify webhook signature with Stripe-Signature header
// Always store raw event in subscription_events table
```

### Subscription States
```ts
type SubscriptionStatus = 'active' | 'inactive' | 'lapsed' | 'cancelled'
// Access gate: only 'active' subscribers can enter draws
// Lapsed = payment failed but not yet cancelled
// Cancelled = explicitly cancelled
```

---

## 8. DRAW ENGINE RULES

### Match Logic
```ts
// /lib/draw-engine/matcher.ts
export function computeMatch(userScores: number[], drawnNumbers: number[]): number {
  return userScores.filter(s => drawnNumbers.includes(s)).length
  // Returns 0–5. Only 3, 4, 5 qualify as winners.
}
```

### Prize Pool
```ts
// /lib/draw-engine/prize-calculator.ts
// 5-match = 40% of pool (jackpot — rolls over if unclaimed)
// 4-match = 35% of pool
// 3-match = 25% of pool
// Split equally among multiple winners in same tier
// Jackpot carry-forward stored in draws.jackpot_carry_in
```

### Draw Modes
```ts
type DrawMode = 'random' | 'algorithmic'
// random: Math.random() based lottery
// algorithmic: weighted by most/least frequent Stableford scores across all active users
// Admin must run simulation before publishing
// Simulation does NOT create winners — only preview
```

