## 12. SECURITY RULES

- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` or `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` to client
- Always verify Stripe webhook signatures — reject unverified requests with 400
- Validate all user input with Zod before any database operation
- Rate limit score entry endpoints — one score per date per user enforced at DB level (unique constraint)
- Admin routes must check `profiles.role = 'admin'` server-side on every request
- Winner proof uploads: validate file type (image only) and size (max 5MB) before Supabase Storage upload

