## 13. ERROR HANDLING PATTERNS

```ts
// API routes — always return typed responses
type ApiResponse<T> = 
  | { success: true; data: T }
  | { success: false; error: string; code?: string }

// Score entry — specific error codes
'DUPLICATE_DATE'      // Score for this date already exists
'INVALID_RANGE'       // Score not between 1–45
'SUBSCRIPTION_LAPSED' // User not active subscriber
'MAX_SCORES_ERROR'    // Should never happen but guard anyway

// Always show user-friendly messages — never expose DB errors to client
```

